The given information can be used to write a quadratic in vertex form, $y = a(x - 5)^2 + 3$. Plugging in our point $(2, 0)$ will help us find $a$.
<span 数学问题: Given a quadratic function $y = a(x - 5)^2 + 3$ with vertex $(5, 3)$ and containing the point $(2, 0)$, find the value of $a$. </math说服: -->
$$
\begin{array}{l}
y=a(x-5)^{2}+3 \\
0=(2-5)^{2}
\end{array}
$$
(Because we know the point $(2,0)$ is such a function, this example demonstrates how a quadratic function can be determined by a point and vertex.)
